Dependency injection is a technique in which the dependency of a class is injected by another class.

In C#, it is done by using the constructor of a class to pass the dependency.

The following example shows how a class "Car" can have a dependency "Engine" and how to inject the Engine into the Car.

```
public class Car
{
    public Car(Engine engine)
    {
        this.Engine = engine;
    }

    public Engine Engine { get; set; }
}

public class Engine
{
    public Engine(Oil oil)
    {
        this.Oil = oil;
    }

    public Oil Oil { get; set; }
}

public class Oil
{
    public Oil() { }
}

public void Main()
{
    Car car = new Car(new Engine(new Oil()));
    car.Drive();
}
```

